content.raw: It is better to allow only loading the P , I, and D values. The other controller values including limitation and etc. should be assigned in the SDF file. This is dangerous since assigning not tuned controller parameters can cause a crash in physics engine.
content.html: It is better to allow only loading the P , I, and D values. The other controller values including limitation and etc. should be assigned in the SDF file. This is dangerous since assigning not tuned controller parameters can cause a crash in physics engine.

content.raw: by setting the ODE step size to 0.01 and running at  100hz , the simulation is not working, now it works with 2000hz. I think it is not possible to control the robots movement precisely with 100hz. I have already spend a lot of time in tuning the ODE and PID parameters to perform movements similar to Simspark. but still , I think it is possible to control the robot with lower gain and effect size and arrange the simulator to work with 1000hz.
